From c263f52d26fa542929bb74b8974cb0efb988c9ae Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ben Browning <bbrownin@redhat.com>
Date: Sat, 13 Jun 2026 00:50:19 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] [Frontend] Replace legacy Gemma4 parsers with engine-based
 implementation

Port the Gemma4 streaming parser to the engine framework, replacing the
legacy reasoning and tool parsers. Gemma4 uses channel-based reasoning
markers and a custom non-JSON argument format with quote-delimited
strings. The engine adapter is registered under the existing "gemma4"
name so no user-facing configuration changes are needed.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>

Signed-off-by: Ben Browning <bbrownin@redhat.com>
